==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impartial
<hw>Im*par"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>partial</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>impartial</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not partial; not favoring one more
than another; treating all alike; unprejudiced; unbiased; disinterested;
equitable; fair; just.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Jove is <qex>impartial</qex>, and to both the same.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A comprehensive and <qex>impartial</qex> view.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impartialist</ent>⟦br⟧
